line.token: * Ensures doc blocks follow basic formatting.
* Ensures doc blocks follow basic formatting.
* A list of tokenizers this sniff supports.
* Returns an array of tokens this test wants to listen for.
* Processes this test, when one of its tokens is encountered.
* @param int $stackPtr The position of the current token
// The first line of the comment should just be the /** code.
'The open comment tag must be the only content on the line'
// The last line of the comment should just be the */ code.
'The close comment tag must be the only content on the line'
// Check for additional blank lines at the end of the comment.
'Additional blank lines found at end of doc comment'
// No extra newline before short description.
'Doc comment short description must be on the first line'
// Account for the fact that a short description might cover
'Doc comment short description must start with a capital letter'
'There must be exactly one blank line between descriptions in a doc comment'
'Doc comment long description must start with a capital letter'
'There must be exactly one blank line before the tags in a doc comment'
// Break out the tags into groups and check alignment within each.
// A tag group is one where there are no blank lines between tags.
// The param tag group is special as it requires all @param tags to be inside.
'Parameter tags must be grouped together in a doc comment'
'Tag cannot be grouped with parameter tags in a doc comment'
// Check for a value. No value means no padding needed.
// Check that there was single blank line after the tag block
// but account for a multi-line tag comments.
'There must be a single blank line after a tag group'
'Tag value indented incorrectly; expected %s spaces but found %s'
// If there is a param group, it needs to be first.
'Parameter tags must be defined first in a doc comment'
'Tags must be grouped together in a doc comment'
